# nyne Path Patterns — Complete Reference

## Root-Level Virtual Files

```
@/GUIDE.md                    # agent-friendly nyne guide (generated)
@/STATUS.md                   # mount status: tier, languages, LSP, cache stats, errors
```

## File-Level Namespace

```
file.{{ ext }}@/OVERVIEW.md                  # symbol table with line ranges
file.{{ ext }}@/lines                        # all lines: read, write (replaces), append (to EOF)
file.{{ ext }}@/lines:M                      # line M: read, write (replaces), rm (deletes line), append (inserts after)
file.{{ ext }}@/lines:M-N                    # range: read, write (replaces range), rm (deletes range), append (inserts after N)
```

Line ranges with `:M-N` are lookup-only — they don't appear in `readdir`.

## File-Level Git

```
file.{{ ext }}@/git/BLAME.md                # per-line authorship
file.{{ ext }}@/git/BLAME.md:M-N            # blame scoped to range (lookup-only)
file.{{ ext }}@/git/CONTRIBUTORS.md         # contributors ranked by line ownership
file.{{ ext }}@/git/LOG.md                  # commit log
file.{{ ext }}@/git/LOG.md:-10              # last 10 commits (lookup-only)
file.{{ ext }}@/git/LOG.md:5-15             # commits 5-15 (lookup-only)
file.{{ ext }}@/git/NOTES.md               # git notes for commits touching this file
file.{{ ext }}@/diff/HEAD.diff              # uncommitted changes
```

## File-Level LSP

```
file.{{ ext }}@/DIAGNOSTICS.md              # all diagnostics as markdown
file.{{ ext }}@/actions/                     # LSP code actions as .diff files
```

## Symbol Namespace

### Structure

```
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/OVERVIEW.md              # symbol listing
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/imports.{{ ext }}               # import block (read, write, append)
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/docstring.txt            # module-level docstring
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/by-kind/                 # type-filtered views
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/by-kind/fn/             # symlinks to all functions
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/by-kind/struct/         # symlinks to all structs
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/at-line/                 # line-to-symbol lookup (lookup-only)
```

### Per-Symbol Files

```
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/body.{{ ext }}             # symbol body (read, write splices back, append inserts after)
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/signature.{{ ext }}        # declaration line (read, write changes signature)
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/docstring.txt       # docstring (read, write, append, truncate clears)
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/OVERVIEW.md         # child symbol listing
```

### Per-Symbol LSP

```
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/callers/            # symlinks to caller symbols
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/CALLERS.md          # caller sites with inline code context
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/deps/               # symlinks to callee/dependency symbols
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/DEPS.md             # callees as markdown
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/references/         # symlinks to all reference sites
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/REFERENCES.md       # reference sites with inline code context
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/declaration/        # symlinks to declaration
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/DECLARATION.md      # declaration as markdown
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/definition/         # symlinks to definition
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/DEFINITION.md       # definition as markdown
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/DOC.md             # hover documentation and type info
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/HINTS.md           # inlay hints
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/actions/           # code actions as .diff files
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/rename/new_name.diff    # rename preview (lookup-only)
```

### Per-Symbol Git

```
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/git/LOG.md         # commits touching this symbol
file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/git/BLAME.md       # per-line authorship scoped to symbol
```

### Filesystem Operations on Symbols

```
rmdir file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/              # delete symbol from source
rm file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo.{{ ext }}          # shorthand — same effect
rm file.{{ ext }}@/lines:10-20                   # delete a line range
mv file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/old@/ file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/new@/   # LSP rename
```

## Git — Repository Level

```
@/git/STATUS.md                # working tree status, staged changes
@/git/branches/                # branch listing
@/git/tags/                    # tag listing
```
